($55)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"Safari Comb ($12)"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"Every other day"}],["$","td","4",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"Minimal change"}]]}],["$","tr","4",{"className":"","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"Short Double"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"Hertzko Slicker ($18)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"FURminator ($35)"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"Weekly + seasonal"}],["$","td","4",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"High seasonal change"}]]}],["$","tr","5",{"className":"","children":[["$","td","0",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"Long Double"}],["$","td","1",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"Chris Christensen ($55)"}],["$","td","2",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"FURminator ($35)"}],["$","td","3",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"Weekly + seasonal"}],["$","td","4",{"className":"border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 ","children":"Extreme seasonal change"}]]}]]}]}]}]
2d:["$","h2","52",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Budget Recommendations by Scenario"}]
2e:["$","p","53",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Minimal budget ($12-18):**\nHertzko slicker brush. Works for most single-coat and short double-coat dogs. Skip seasonal deshedding during major sheds."}]
2f:["$","p","54",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Moderate budget ($35-55):**\nHertzko slicker ($18) + FURminator ($35). Handles most coat types year-round. Good for owners willing to invest in seasonal maintenance."}]
30:["$","p","55",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**Serious grooming budget ($55+):**\nChris Christensen slicker ($55) + FURminator ($35) + Safari comb ($12). Professional-grade setup. Handles any coat type, especially long double coats."}]
31:["$","h2","56",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Mistakes to Avoid"}]
32:["$","p","57",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**1. Using a FURminator year-round on double coats** — It can damage the topcoat if used too frequently. Limit to heavy shedding seasons."}]
33:["$","p","58",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**2. Slicker brushing against the grain** — Always brush in the direction of hair growth. Brushing backward causes discomfort and can damage hair shafts."}]
34:["$","p","59",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**3. Skipping undercoat work on double-coat dogs** — Loose undercoat tangles into the topcoat and creates painful mats. Regular deshedding prevents this."}]
35:["$","p","60",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**4. Using single-coat tools on double-coat dogs** — The teeth aren't spaced correctly for reaching undercoat. You'll miss most of the shed hair."}]
36:["$","p","61",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"**5. Grooming a dry double-coat dog** — Mist with water first. Dry deshedding can cause breakage, especially with long coats."}]
37:["$","h2","62",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Conclusion"}]
38:["$","p","63",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"The right deshedding tool depends entirely on your dog's coat type. For single-coat breeds, a simple slicker brush is sufficient. For double-coat breeds, especially long-haired ones, invest in both a slicker brush for maintenance and a FURminator for seasonal undercoat removal."}]
39:["$","p","64",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"Start with a Hertzko slicker ($18) as your baseline tool—it works for most dogs. If your dog has a double coat and sheds heavily, add a FURminator ($35). If your dog has a long coat (any type), upgrade to the Chris Christensen slicker ($55) for professional-grade results."}]
3a:["$","p","65",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"Deshedding is an investment of time, but the payoff in a cleaner home and healthier dog coat is enormous."}]
